messages.subject: RE: [AlwaysLearning] 6 Degrees of Separation
messages.msgSnippet: I ve printed your message Susan, and I m giving it to Jeanne tomorrow morning at rehearsal.  Also, I e-mailed Kathleen and she sent her hello s back to Karen
messages.messageBody:
I've printed your message Susan, and I'm giving it to Jeanne tomorrow
morning at rehearsal. Also, I e-mailed Kathleen and she sent her
hello's back to Karen Tucker (do you go by Karen or Tuck?). Said you
(Karen Tucker) were the kind of person she knew immediately she was
going to like - that you had no hidden agenda's. Seems that everybody
loves everybody in our homeschool theatre groups! VBG!

Laurel

-----Original Message-----
From: Susan Bundlie [mailto:strandbe@...]
Sent: Monday, April 08, 2002 9:20 AM
To: AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [AlwaysLearning] 6 Degrees of Separation


And speaking of making conenctions:

<<Wow! It's like 6 degrees of separation! ...It was already so much
fun with
Jeanne, the VA director...>>

I can't believe I read this! I have been looking for Jeanne for two
years! I found her name somehow back in '98 or '99 as someone connected
with homeschool theater and we corresponded for awhile. Then my computer

crashed and I lost addresses and couldn't remember hers. No amount of
searching helped, since I didn't know her last name. I rememered YPT and

knew the general area (east coast), but couldn't find anything about
that either.

Laurel, would you mention me to Jeanne and ask her if she'd like to send

an e-mail sometime? (Susan -- strandbe@...) Thanks! I love
coincidences.

Susan
